feat(invitations): add invitation reactivation endpoint

Add POST /v1/households/:householdId/invitations/:invitationId/reactivate endpoint to reactivate expired invitations with automatic email delivery.

**Database (Migration 014):**
- Add reactivation_count INTEGER column to household_invitations
- Add invitation_reactivated to audit event actions enum

**Domain Layer:**
- Update Invitation entity with reactivationCount field
- Create ReactivateInvitationUseCase with business rules:
  * Only caregivers can reactivate invitations
  * Only expired invitations can be reactivated
  * Maximum 3 reactivations per invitation (prevents abuse)
  * Generates new token with 72-hour expiration

**Data Layer:**
- Implement reactivateInvitation in PostgresHouseholdRepository
- Implement reactivateInvitation in InMemoryHouseholdRepository
- Update mapInvitation helper to include reactivationCount

**API Layer:**
- Add POST /invitations/:id/reactivate route handler
- Automatic email queuing after reactivation
- Audit logging for invitation_reactivated action
- Returns full invitation details with new token and links

This feature enables caregivers to reactivate expired invitations without creating duplicates, while preventing abuse through rate limiting.
